programme.title: Breakfast
programme.desc: Round-up of national and international news, plus the latest from the money markets(n).(n)

programme.title: Oxford Street Revealed
programme.desc: Transport for London's ticket inspectors battle fare dodgers, deal with verbal abuse and a host of grumpy passengers, while park ranger Paul deals with lost property, gate closures and Second Word War bunkers. Plus, as Elf the Musical opens at the Dominion Theatre various support workers along the thoroughfare brace themselves for the impact on their workload(n).(n)

programme.title: Homes Under the Hammer
programme.desc: Developers Lucy Alexander and Martin Roberts explore properties about to be auctioned, then follow the sale and talk to the buyers about their plans for the buildings. A family modernises a semi-detached property in Shropshire, while a young property developer updates a flat in Folkestone, Kent, to raise money for travelling. Finally, a property development company takes just four weeks to update a bungalow in Cornwall(n).(n)

programme.title: The Secret Life of the Hospital Bed
programme.desc: A 67-year-old farmer arrives in Birmingham for much-needed surgery on his leg, while in Newcastle, a 12-year-old boy is treated for a suspected broken wrist(n).(n)

programme.title: Rip Off Britain: Food
programme.desc: The true cost of Britain's fish and chips is revealed and how some of the lagers that trade off their foreign roots actually have their origins rather closer to home(n).(n)

programme.title: Bargain Hunt
programme.desc: Radio 1 DJs Dev Griffin and Alice Levine and Radio 4 presenters Nick Robinson and Aasmah Mir battle it out in east London's Spitalfields market in aid of BBC Children in Need. Experts David Harper and Christina Trevanion join in the fun, alongside presenter Natasha Raskin(n).(n)

programme.title: Doctors
programme.desc: Rob and Tyler are called to investigate a robbery at some sheltered accommodation and Al has doubts about the advice he gave to a patient(n).(n)

programme.title: Moving On
programme.desc: A timid man is pressed into a potentially hostile situation after his wife insists he speak to the noisy builders threatening to ruin a family occasion. John inevitably mismanages the situation, prompting his confrontational brother Darren to go on the warpath instead, while John secretly enjoys following his brother's lead. However, the situation soon leads to a dramatic stand-off. Drama, starring William Ash and Rebecca Callard. Last in the series(n).(n)

programme.title: Escape to the Country
programme.desc: Property expert Jules Hudson helps a recently retired couple relocate to the Cornwall countryside in order for them to be closer to their daughter and her family. Jules also takes time out to pay a visit to one of the oldest seal sanctuaries in the country(n).(n)

programme.title: Money for Nothing
programme.desc: Sarah Moore saves three more items from the recycling centre in Witley, Surrey, with master craftsman Jay Blades revamping a discarded chair and artisan Norman Wilkinson using old floorboards to transform a chest of drawers(n).(n)

programme.title: Flog It
programme.desc: Experts Caroline Hawley and James Lewis value items brought in to Wolverhampton Art Gallery, while presenter Paul Martin finds out about the life of footballer Billy Wright(n).(n)

programme.title: Pointless
programme.desc: Quiz show in which pairs of contestants try to score the fewest points possible by giving the least obvious correct answers to questions posed to 100 people before the show. At the end of each round, the team with the most points is eliminated until the final two pairs battle for the chance to compete for a cash prize. Presented by Alexander Armstrong and Richard Osman(n).(n)

programme.title: The One Show
programme.desc: A guest co-host joins Alex Jones to present the final edition of the week, featuring the usual mix of celebrity guests and stories about people in extraordinary circumstances(n).(n)

programme.title: Children in Need
programme.desc: Tess Daly and Greg James introduce a night of entertainment as the BBC's annual appeal night gets under way, beginning with a performance from the hit West End musical Aladdin and a special children's edition of Would I Lie to You? 8.00 The cast of EastEnders performs a dance medley of 1980s movie classics and a children's choir of over 1,500 members sings in unison across the nation. Plus, an exclusive first look at the Doctor Who Christmas special. 8.30 Graham Norton and Ade Adepitan host as a group of children receives a very special surprise from Little Mix. Plus, an Olympic-themed Strictly Come Dancing featuring some of the members of Team GB. 9.00 Mel Giedroyc and Sue Perkins help Oscar-winning actor Eddie Redmayne in his quest to find Pudsey Bear. 9.30 The final leg of The One Show's amazing rickshaw challenge. Plus, the first winner of The Sir Terry Wogan Fundraiser of Year Award is announced and Craig David is in the studio to perform the official Children in Need single, All We Needed. Continues on BBC Two and concludes on BBC One at 10.40pm(n).(n)

programme.title: Children in Need
programme.desc: Marvin and Rochelle Humes host, introducing a special performance by Little Mix and offering an exclusive sneak peak of Call the Midwife's Christmas special. Plus, Swedish singer-songwriter Zara Larsson performs in the studio. 11.00 A comedy dance performance by the cast of Citizen Khan and a further appearance by the cast of Aladdin. 11.30 Comedian Russell Kane joins in the fun, plus Busted perform in the studio. 12.00 The casts of West End musicals Motown and Half a Sixpence perform, before the all-important final total is revealed(n).(n)

programme.title: Children in Need Rocks for Terry
programme.desc: Fearne Cotton and Greg James host a special concert staged at the Royal Albert Hall to honour broadcaster and Children in Need figurehead Terry Wogan, featuring performances by Take That, Ellie Goulding, Olly Murs, Gregory Porter, Michael Ball, Alfie Boe, Rick Astley, Beverley Knight, Alexander Armstrong, the Vamps, Ward Thomas and Shaun Escoffery. There are also appeal films and archive clips of Terry's career, including a chance to relive one of the classic Radio 2 Janet and John Stories(n).(n)

programme.title: Live International Rugby Union
programme.desc: Wales v Japan (Kick-off 2.30pm). Gabby Logan presents coverage of the third autumn international fixture for the hosts, who welcome the Cherry Blossoms to Principality Stadium. programme.title: Children in Need
programme.sub-title: Children in Need - The Best Bits.
programme.desc: Ade Adepitan presents highlights from last night's fundraising extravaganza, including a Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them sketch, and the cast of EastEnders performing a dance medley of 1980s movie classics. Plus, the Olympic heroes of Team GB take part in a special edition of Strictly Come Dancing. Also features music by Little Mix, Craig David, and the cast of Aladdin(n).(n)

programme.title: Strictly Come Dancing
programme.desc: Tess Daly, Claudia Winkleman and the Strictly entourage head to Blackpool's world-famous Tower Ballroom, the spiritual home of dancing, for this week's edition. Over the years its elegant surroundings have been host to thousands of amateur and professional dancers - and tonight the tradition continues as the celebrity hoofers and their partners battle to get their names at the top of the leaderboard and avoid the fate of last week's eliminated couple Daisy and Aljaz. As they perform a mixture of routines, they'll be hoping to impress judges Len Goodman, Bruno Tonioli, Craig Revel Horwood and Darcey Bussell, but they'll also need viewers' votes to keep them out of tomorrow's dreaded dance-off(n).(n)

programme.title: Michael McIntyre's Big Show
programme.desc: New series. The lively comedian's family entertainment series returns, as Michael invites more stars to perform in front of a live audience at London's Theatre Royal on Drury Lane. For this first edition, chart-topping, Grammy-nominated singer Ellie Goulding performs, and the cast of Andrew Lloyd Webber's new West End production School of Rock also take to the stage. An unsuspecting member of the public is dragged into the limelight when they become the Unexpected Star of the Show, and Michael gets up to more mischief when Olly Murs hands over his smartphone in Celebrity Send to All(n).(n)

programme.title: Casualty
programme.desc: Grace wakes up, and seems well enough to go home, but Connie is terrified the consultants are letting her leave because they have given up on her recovery. Unable to process the future for her daughter, Connie chooses to work rather than being with her, but when Hugo - an 11-year-old boy who claims to be one of Grace's schoolmates - arrives in the ED after attempting a dangerous hitchhiking trick, Connie is forced to face the reality of her situation. Meanwhile, Elle reveals the team is due to receive an undercover inspection, and Duffy tells Charlie she has asked her husband for a divorce(n).(n)

programme.title: The National Lottery Live
programme.desc: The all-important winning Lotto and Thunderball numbers are revealed, as Alexander Armstrong joins Kate Garraway to do the honours and presses the button(n).(n)

programme.title: Match of the Day
programme.desc: Gary Lineker presents highlights of the latest Premier League matches, including Manchester United v Arsenal, and Sunderland v Hull City. This has been one of the standout fixtures on the football calendar since the dawn of the Premier League era, and this season is no different, especially as it allows Jose Mourinho and Arsene Wenger to continue their rivalry, and the Red Devils are looking to play catch-up with the Gunners. Meanwhile, two teams ensconced in what appears to be a battle to avoid relegation faced each other, as The Black Cats hosted the Tigers(n).(n)

programme.title: This World
programme.desc: Filmmaker James Jones conducts a forensic investigation into the death of William Chapman, the black teenager who was shot dead in Portsmouth, Virginia, by white police officer Stephen Rankin on April 22, 2015. As a result of the incident, Rankin was fired from Portsmouth Police Department, and was charged with first-degree murder, but Jones reveals that Chapman was only one of 306 black men killed by police in the US last year, and only 14 officers have faced charges. Making use of access to both prosecution and defence lawyers, as well as to both Rankin and Chapman's family and friends, Jones documents the unfolding drama of Rankin's trial, and sets his story against the wider socio-political conflict causing tension between black communities and the authorities across America today(n).(n)

Thriller, based on a true story, starring Clint Eastwood, Patrick McGoohan, Roberts Blossom and Fred Ward(n).(n)

Wolfgang Petersen's thriller, starring Clint Eastwood, John Malkovich, Rene Russo and Dylan McDermott(n).(n)

Fact-based gangster drama, starring Johnny Depp, Benedict Cumberbatch, Joel Edgerton, Dakota Johnson and Kevin Bacon(n).(n)

Thriller, starring Nicolas Cage, Angelina Jolie, Giovanni Ribisi and Robert Duvall(n).(n)

programme.title: Valkyrie
programme.desc: Fact-based thriller, recreating the 1944 plot to assassinate Adolf Hitler using a briefcase bomb. Sci-fi drama, starring Domhnall Gleeson, Alicia Vikander and Oscar Isaac(n).(n)

Drama, directed by and starring Clint Eastwood. With Christopher Carley and Bee Vang(n).(n)

Milos Forman's Oscar-winning drama based on Ken Kesey's novel, starring Jack Nicholson, Louise Fletcher, Brad Dourif and Danny DeVito(n).(n)

Ken Russell's historical drama, starring Oliver Reed and Vanessa Redgrave(n).(n)

Stanley Kubrick's Oscar-winning epic, with Kirk Douglas, Tony Curtis, Laurence Olivier, Jean Simmons, Charles Laughton and Peter Ustinov(n).(n)

Period drama based on David Ebershoff's novel inspired by the true story of artist Lili Elbe, starring Eddie Redmayne and an Oscar-winning Alicia Vikander(n).(n)

The first part of Quentin Tarantino's two-part martial arts thriller, starring Uma Thurman, Lucy Liu, Vivica A Fox, Daryl Hannah and David Carradine(n).(n)

programme.title: Kill Bill: Vol 2
programme.desc: Hitwoman the Bride continues her relentless quest to exact revenge on the group responsible for trying to kill her. Thriller, starring Jane Fonda, Michael Douglas, Jack Lemmon and Scott Brady(n).(n)

Romantic drama based on Sara Gruen's novel, with Reese Witherspoon, Robert Pattinson and Christoph Waltz(n).(n)

Fantasy adventure, with Ryan Reynolds and Jeff Bridges(n).(n)

Action adventure, starring James McAvoy, Angelina Jolie and Morgan Freeman(n).(n)

programme.title: House of Flying Daggers
programme.desc: Two imperial officers are sent to find the head of a rebel group, which threatens to destroy the Tang dynasty's tenuous grip on power. Romantic period martial arts adventure from director Zhang Yimou, starring Zhang Ziyi, Takeshi Kaneshiro, Andy Lau and Song Dandan. In Mandarin(n).(n)

Instead he challenges him to compete in a shooting competition to win a superb rifle, but when the murderer loses, he steals the coveted prize. Western, starring James Stewart, Shelley Winters, Dan Duryea and Stephen McNally(n).(n)

programme.title: ParaNorman

When a curse placed on the town by a witch centuries ago causes zombies to rise from the grave, it falls to the youngster to avert disaster. Animated adventure, with the voices of Kodi Smit-McPhee and John Goodman(n).(n)

programme.title: Short Circuit 2
programme.desc: Manic mechanoid Johnny Five meets an old friend in New York City and embarks on a fact-finding tour - but ends up entangled in a series of escapades culminating in a bank robbery. Sci-fi comedy sequel, starring Fisher Stevens, Michael McKean, Cynthia Gibb and Jack Weston, with the voice of Tim Blaney(n).(n)

Driven from his home by his terrified mother, the bewildered youngster trapped in a grown-up body makes his way to New York, where he rises high in the ranks of a toy manufacturing company and applies his youthful enthusiasm to the complexities of adult life. Comedy, starring Tom Hanks, Elizabeth Perkins and Robert Loggia(n).(n)

Romantic comedy, with Brittany Murphy, Ashton Kutcher, Christian Kane and David Moscow(n).(n)

Sci-fi thriller, starring Joel Courtney and Elle Fanning(n).(n)

Fantasy adventure, starring Aaron Eckhart, Bill Nighy and Miranda Otto(n).(n)

Crime comedy, starring Tony Danza, Lea Thompson and Betty White(n).(n)

Family drama, starring Sherilyn Fenn, Hume Cronyn and Rory Culkin(n).(n)

Romantic comedy sequel to A Golden Christmas, with Julie Gonzalo, KC Clyde, Bruce Davison and Alley Mills(n).(n)

Festive fantasy, starring Art Carney, Jaclyn Smith, Paul Le Mat and Mason Adams(n).(n)

Trini Alvarado also stars in Sally Field's directorial debut(n).(n)

programme.title: The Christmas Choir
programme.desc: A workaholic accountant is forced to reassess his priorities after his devotion to his job costs him his girlfriend. An encounter with a homeless pianist reminds him of his forgotten dream of becoming a musician, so he decides to help the residents of a homeless shelter earn some money by forming a choir. Drama, starring Jason Gedrick and Tyrone Benskin(n).(n)

programme.title: The Christmas Gift

But before long, their warm welcome by the residents begins to melt his frosty facade, turning him against his boss and the company's unscrupulous plans. Drama, starring John Denver, Jane Kaczmarek and Kurtwood Smith(n).(n)

Comedy drama, starring Harry Hamlin, William Hootkins and Megan Gallagher(n).(n)

programme.title: The Waltons

programme.desc: Mrs Griggs decides that a 'social skills' class could be beneficial for certain pupils - including Martha, Rufus, Cassie and Maxwell. When Mrs Griggs tells Martha a winning personality as well as academic achievement is vital in order to get into a top university, Martha panics and is determined to succeed in the social skills class and prove she does indeed have a winning personality. Mrs Griggs volunteers a reluctant Mr Malone to take the classes and hands him a book written by her beloved 'Guru Holeman' called Being Whole as a manual to help him. When Lily is mistakenly led to believe by Jas that Matt is emigrating to Australia she is distraught that he hasn't even told her he's leaving. She becomes convinced it's because she's too easy-going that he hasn't even bothered to tell her. She begs Mrs Griggs to let her go to social skills class, too, so she can learn to be less easy-going. Ollie is then sent there for being too pompous and Jas for being too exuberant. Worn down, eventually Mr Malone has had enough of teaching the class Mrs Griggs' way. He throws the book in the bin and gives the pupils a new exercise of his own - wearing blindfolds so they can feel free without worrying how people see them. It works - a blindfolded Lily is able to tell Matt she'll really miss him when he emigrates, which prompts Matt to tell her that he's not going anywhere. And Martha realises she's doing just fine with the personality she already has(n).(n)

In their attempts to find rogue robots, Cain pitches his theory that - given the multiple incidents involving robot activity at the Clarke house, plus Nick's prior history with Mary Douglas - this is a good place to start. When the doorbell rings, Eve answers to find Cain and Michael. Detecting their concealed EMPs, she slams the door on them. Spooked by this odd behaviour they break in, fearful that there may be another robot siege in progress. Once inside they learn that Eve is the robot and blast her with their EMPs - only for time to rewind. This has simply been a simulation in Eve's predictive software! Eve runs multiple simulations trying to find a way to stop Cain and Michael discovering her robot nature, but in each one her identity is exposed and Cain and Michael destroy her. With time running out, Eve recruits the Will and Lily simulations. Lily speculates that Eve is experiencing anxiety. She has become so human, that it has caused her predictive software to malfunction. Eve must disable the software and go it alone. Although Eve manages to evade discovery, neither she nor the gang realise that, while inside, Cain has bugged Nick's computer and is one step closer to the truth(n).(n)
